    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.1515/1088: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-25T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 25, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. I have just received a note from the President of the Republic, dated June
                    23, stating that he has received a telegram from the Honduranean delegation in
                    Washington to the effect that the Department’s proposal that the competency of
                    the Central American Tribunal to try the boundary question be submitted to a
                    special tribunal has been, accepted with the understanding that both parties
                    will abide by the decision of the special tribunal.</p>
                <p>The President’s note then adds that although the Honduranean delegates have ample
                    powers to act as they think best he has recommended that they observe the
                    greatest harmony with the impartial opinion of the Department of State
                    “principally with reference to the acceptance of the special treaty of juridical
                    arbitration”.</p>
                <p>In view of the above message from the Honduranean delegation he states that he
                    has decided not to call for the present the meeting mentioned in my telegram No.
                    49, June 22, 7 p.m.<note n="82" xml:id="d325fn82">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
